  '5b361174-c9ab-426e-8340-8b11cf43da7d',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$Kotlin Dependency Injection ‚Äî Hilt vs Koin$escape$,
  $escape$Dependency injection (DI) is crucial for maintaining a clean, modular, and scalable Android codebase in Kotlin. It helps reduce boilerplate code, improves testability, and simplifies maintenance. Both Hilt and Koin are popular DI libraries for Kotlin Android development. Hilt, developed by Google, provides a more seamless integration with Android components, while Koin offers a more lightweight and flexible solution. When choosing between Hilt and Koin, consider the size and complexity of your project, as well as your team's familiarity with each library.$escape$,
  $escape$null$escape$,
  $escape$kotlin$escape$,
